<br>
Sorry, but that's just not true, particularly for a game as texture-intensive as EQ. At 1600x1200x32 with no anti-aliasing you're using 21MB of RAM just for the display and depth buffer, before you even add any textures. I don't know what texture size EQ uses, but it has a texture for each player and a single 512x512x32 texture takes up another megabyte, or one and a half megabytes with mip-mapping. RAM goes fast if you want a high-quality image. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8555.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8555.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=8555.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=8555.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8555.topic&index=47><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.threadControl?topicID=8555.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8555.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8555.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="